<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <title>Read Books list</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/index.css">
</head>
<body>
        <h1>Biru Skai</h1>
        <h2>Books I have read</h2>
        <p class="text">
                A project from udemy for web development. This project is a copy of the original idea from <a href="https://sive.rs/book" target="_blank">Derek Sivers</a>.<br>
                The purpose is to learn how to develop a website based on html, css, express, ejs, axios and pg.
                In the future this website's content may have relevant changes after the web developer has read books. 
        </p>

        <p class="text">
                Tiny summary but detailed notes for each. Use the ISBN number to find it from your local library or anywhere else. 
                This page will constantly update as I read more, so bookmark it if you want to check back in a few months.
        </p>
        <p class="text">
                Sorted with my top recommendations up top. Sort by 
                <a href="/?sort=title">title</a>, 
                <a href="/?sort=newest">newest</a>, or 
                <a href="/?sort=rating">best</a>.
        </p><hr>

        <a href="/add" id="addBook">Add Book</a>

        <div>
                <% if (locals.dataBooks.length > 0) { %>
                        <% dataBooks.map((book) => { %>
                        <div class="bookContainer">
                                <div>
                                        <ul>
                                                <li><a href="/update/<%= book.id %>" class="modify">Update</a></li>
                                                <li><form method="post" action="/delete/<%= book.id %>"><input class="modify" type="submit" name="delete" value="Delete"></form></li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <img src="https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/<%= book.isbn %>-M.jpg" alt="book Image: <%= book.title %>"/>
                                </div>
                                <div class="contentContainer">
                                        <h2><a href="/notes/<%= book.id %>"><%= book.title %> - by <%= book.author %></a></h2>
                                        <small>
                                                Date read: <%= book.time %>.<br> 
                                                How strongly I recommend it: <strong><%= book.rating %></strong>/10
                                        </small>
                
                                        <p class="text"><%= book.summary %></p>
                                        <p class="text"><strong><a href="/notes/<%= book.id %>">Read my notes</a></strong>, or go to the <a href="<%= book.website %>">Amazon page</a> for details and reviews.</p>
                                </div>
                        </div>
                        <% }) %>
                <% } else { %>
                        <p>Book list is empty</p>
                <% } %>
        </div>

</body>
</html>